<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.221073>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 4. Aculepeira morenoae n. sp., habitus. 1 – 2, female holotype (1, dorsal; 2, ventral). 3 – 4, male paratype (3, dorsal; 4, ventral)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/221073/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.221075>
    dc:description "FIGURES 7 – 12. Aculepeira morenoae n. sp., female genitalia. 7 – 9, epigynum (7, ventral; 8, lateral; 9, digested ventral). 10 – 12, digested vulva (10, posterior; 11, anterior; 12, dorsal)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/221075/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.221076>
    dc:description "FIGURES 13 – 15. Aculepeira morenoae n. sp., left palp. 13, prolateral; 14, ventral; 15, retrolateral. (c = conductor; cy = cymbium; e = embolus; ma = median apophysis; pc = paracymbium; sa = subterminal apophysis; ta = terminal apophysis; * = flagellae of ma; + = dentate end of ma). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/221076/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.221077>
    dc:description "FIGURES 16 – 23. Aculepeira morenoae n. sp., expanded left palp. 16 – 18, ventral from different angle; 19, prolateral; 20, retrolateral; 21, retrolateral-basal; 22, prolateral-apical; 23, apical. (bh = basal hematodocha; c = conductor; cy = cymbium; dh = distal hematodocha; e = embolus; f = fundus; ma = median apophysis; pc = paracymbium; r = radix; sa = subterminal apophysis; sd = sperm duct; t = tegulum; ta = terminal apophysis; * = flagellae of ma; + = dentate end of ma)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/221077/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.221078>
    dc:description "FIGURES 24 – 30. Aculepeira morenoae n. sp., left palp SEM. 24, retrolateral-ventral; 25, retrolateral; 26, dorsal; 27, apical; 28 – 30, close up views (28, median apophysis; 29 – 30, dentate end of median apophysis. (c = conductor; cy = cymbium; e = embolus; ma = median apophysis; pc = paracymbium; sa = subterminal apophysis; ta = terminal apophysis; * = flagellae of ma; + = dentate end of ma). Scale bars: 0.5 mm" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/221078/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.221074>
    dc:description "FIGURES 5 – 6. Aculepeira morenoae n. sp., frontal view. 5, female holotype. 6, male paratype." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/221074/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.221079>
    dc:description "FIGURES 31 – 32. Flooding pampas grasses in Campos del Tuyú National Park, Buenos Aires, habitat of Aculepeira morenoae n. sp. 31, panoramic view looking northeast; 32, grasses where spiders inhabit." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/221079/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

